text.section:
An administrative law judge:
shall be a special appointment in the State Personnel Management System;
may be removed, suspended, or demoted by the Chief Administrative Law Judge for cause, after notice and an opportunity to be heard;
shall receive the compensation provided in the State budget; and
may not perform duties inconsistent with the duties and responsibilities of an administrative law judge.

In any contested case conducted by an administrative law judge, the administrative law judge may:
authorize the issuance of subpoenas for witnesses;
administer oaths;
examine an individual under oath; and
compel the production of documents or other tangible things.
